cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.DB 

This paper is primarily focused on clinical information retrieval using electronic health records. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to extract relevant information from the EHRs, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural network representation learning frameworks, which can be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Furthermore, the paper deals with data management and storage of EHRs, which can be categorized under cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper discusses the use of distant supervision, which can be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
